Package com.im.njams.sdk.configuration

Class Configuration

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.im.njams.sdk.configuration.Configuration
  • public class Configuration
extends Object
    The configuration contains all configuration of the client, which are not part of the initial settings, and therefore could be changed by the client instance, or via instructions.
    Author:
    pnientiedt

        public ProcessConfiguration getProcess​(String processPath)
        Return the ProcessConfiguration, which contains all settings for a process.
        Parameters:
        processPath - The path of the process for that a configuration shall be returned.

      • hasProcessExcludeFilter

        public boolean hasProcessExcludeFilter​(Path processPath)
        Returns true only if there is a specific exclude setting for given process.
        This is not the same as isProcessExcluded(Path) since there may be additional filters that lead to excluding this process.
        This method is mainly for processing configuration commands from nJAMS server.
        Parameters:
        processPath - The process path to test
        Returns:
        Whether there is a specific exclude filter for the given process.
        See Also:
        ProcessFilter.hasExcludeFilter(Path)

      • setProcessExcluded

        public void setProcessExcluded​(Path processPath,
                               boolean excluded)
        Sets an exclude filter for the given process, or removes it according to the given exclude parameter.
        Parameters:
        processPath - The process path for that an exclude shall be updated
        excluded - If true, an exclude filter is set, otherwise it's removed.
        See Also:
        ProcessFilter.setExcluded(Path, boolean)
